Description: An oval jar-seal: of pale brown clay, bearing seal impressions on either side, one giving the repeated name of Anedjib, and the other the name of the official, Sabu. Good condition, slightly broken at edges.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Tomb of Den, Excavator's mark 'T'

Kaplony, 'Die Inschriften der Ägyptischen Frühzeit III (Wiesbaden, 1964), pls.57, abb.205;73, abb. 274; see also vols. I, 137 and II, 814, n. 791; 1120, 1129.
